task.summary: Default task
Still tracking down uncommitted files.
Improvements, Added a head function, tests. Might have improved logging output.
Found small annoying edge case in parser. Many impovements to documentation both outside and inside QDL. Syntax check function added so can check scripts more easily.
Check in for 5.0.2
Set version numbers
Improvements, Added a head function, tests.
Updating version numbers in PDFs
Checkin before fixes for 5.0.3
5.0.3 branch creations
Version 5.0.3 fixes
Merge from 5.0.3
Minor change. Want to keep in sync with other changes and do a push.
CIL-708 fixes
Added a post_ pre_ exchange execution phase to give better control of when scripts can execute.
removed insanely verbose debugging in cleanup threads. Fixed a bug in managing claims.
Tweaks to stores to make it easier to access things.
Added serialization improvements to help with stored state in scripting.
Found a java version bug relating to XML.
QDL improvements to module serialization.
Improvements, Added a head function, tests.
Updated documents, improved saving and loading state.
improvements to tokens, added ability to do turn low level debugging off and on in CLIs (long overdue).
Added better state tracking with complex tokens.
Many small improvements to template handling as well as the command line client (which is actually getting to be a pretty darned slick and useful tool).
Many improvements. Documentation in CL client, making execution more modular. Added some constants.
Found and fixed regression bug for functors.
More tracking claims in the correct leg.
Found and fixed a bug in client approvals. Moved a utility class so it was visible in more packages. Lots of little tweaks to command line clients. Better messages on errors and such.
Many little fixes, but mostly this is a re-working of the error handling to fix CIL-697.
Upcoming changes to configuration file handling. These are isolated and have zero effect on current code but should get committed.
More tests. Added an exception. renamed a class
Final checkin before cutting release. Just added some tests.
5.1.0 checkin
Slight modification for new error handling.
Argh somehow a critical conditional got deleted. Reinstating.
Changed how some thigns are listed, added a small optimization for certain conditionals + tests. More documentation upgrades.
More tests. Added an exception. renamed a class
IDE upgrade caused some oddness in version numbers, so I am committing this now. Also, first cut of RFC 8628 impl.
CIL-922: All tokens are now base 64 encoded, since there were issues with people not properly escaping the new ones or doing surgery on them.
Base 32 encoding of tokens, fix for multi-step LDAP lookup.
Slight clean up, added convenience to CLI. Fixed small QDL serialization bug for edge case
CIL-806 and CIL-890 custom token issuer first cut
CIL-806 and FNAl issues
Fixed small (edge case) QDL bug. Added regression tests for it.
IOInterface not getting propagated to cloned workspaces fixed.
Found and fixed parser issue that required upgrading Antlr from 4.7.2 to 4.9.1. Moar tests! Added basic lambda support to QDL.
More tweaks. Getting information in workspace about modules. Improving help. Found IDE was compiling with old version of Antlr, so had to redo all generated code again.
Addition to parser to support more types of expressions. Unit tests.
More tests. Final touches before next release.
